 to early Christian texts. Are we entering a new age of interpretation of the massive literary production by early Christians, and how does this relate to the traditional disciplines of patristics and church history?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aChristian literature, EarlyxHistory and criticism. 0aFathers of the church. 4aChristliche Literatur. 4aKanon. 4aLate antiquity. 4aMarkion. 4aPatristik. 4aSpätantike. 4aearly Christianity and church history. 4apostclassical Greek literature. 4atheology. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh1 aCameron, Averil, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2016z9783110485097oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104314760 cprintz978311037405640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311043138440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110431384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110431384.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016